Fernando Torres has been left out of Chelsea's squad to face Leicester at Stamford Bridge on Saturday.

The Spanish striker was an unused substitute in Chelsea's 3-1 win over Burnley on Monday night and has been linked with a Stamford Bridge exit this summer.

Jose Mourinho has brought in both Diego Costa and Didier Drogba during the transfer window, bolstering his team's attacking options.

